review_blob: Great visual beer with a thick full head. Aroma is very appealing with notes of apricot, pine, citrus, and hops. Well balanced flavor of apricot with a hoppy finish. Overall a great mix of fruit and hops.
Smells of citrus and pine. Tastes fuller than it smells with hints of sweet barley and a hoppy finish. On tap @ Issaquah brewhouse.
Strong earthy tones with a complex combination of nuts and spices. A lingering flavor of barley and hops stays with you. On tap @ Issaquah brewhouse.
beer_name: Rogue Big Ass Barrel Strong Ale
